key "Ros11"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\E_{0}$
\end_inset

 is the expectation operator with respect to an approximating distribution
 (for example, Poisson).
 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{0}:\mathcal{F}\mapsto\mathcal{H}$
\end_inset

 is the characterizing operator of that distribution (for example, 
\begin_inset Formula $f\mapsto\left(k\mapsto\lambda f\left(k+1\right)-kf\left(k\right)\right)$
\end_inset

).
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{0}$
\end_inset

